transcript_text: Little push workout that I did today that I wanted to share with you all started off with some shoulders stability prep  This will probably be individual for everyone facing the weaknesses  Then I moved to my main compounds which were paused bench and pause the largest press  Lairson press as you can see is good for isolating just the upper pushing muscles  After lairson press I moved the landmine to segway into some overhead dumbbell work  My feet are against the wall here to isolate the shoulders more and set my posture  I finished my pressing with sets of closed grip tempo pushups to failure squeezing the chest at the top  And I super-centred those with del reasons to failure  Form looks a bit cut there because my left shoulder is my bad one
